## Session Start Behaviour

Before responding to the first user message of a new session, call `search_knowledge` to prime context:

```
search_knowledge({
  query: "recent decisions architecture session context",
  projectId: "<PROJECT-ID>",
  minSimilarity: 0.1
})
```

This is the **interim priming mechanism**. It will be replaced by agent-lore's DDR-004 `PromptAssembler` when that ships. Until then, this manual search is how memories enter context.

---

## Search Tuning

- Default `minSimilarity` is **0.1** (lowered from 0.7 in the gateway-dogfood-fixes sprint).
- Short memory entries (1–3 sentences) may score below 0.1 — fall back to `0.05` if results are sparse.

---

## Capture Behaviour

After meaningful turns — a decision, discovery, deviation, or HALT — call `capture_memory` with:

- `projectId: "<PROJECT-ID>"`
- `author: "<AGENT-NAME>"`
- `documentType` ∈ {`spec`, `decision`, `halt`, `discovery`, `test-result`, `review`}
- `epistemicType` ∈ {`FACT`, `EXPERIENCE`, `OPINION`, `OBSERVATION`}
- `status` (optional) ∈ {`draft`, `locked`, `archived`}
- `supersedesId` (optional) — UUID of a prior capture this replaces; makes the new doc canonical

Capture what a future session would need to pick up where this one left off. Do not capture trivial state, ephemeral debugging, or content that the code itself already documents.

