## Relay Dispatcher (optional)

The Relay Dispatcher carries inter-agent messages over the shared LORE store. Two use cases:

1. **Multi-agent coordination between Claude Code sessions** — multiple Lorekeepers working on related repos can hand off context, request captures, or coordinate without each spawning their own Switchboard.
2. **Bridging Claude Desktop to the shared store** — gives a Desktop agent the same memory surface as Claude Code.

Optional in both cases — the Gateway MCP works independently. Run the dispatcher only when one of the above applies.

```bash
RELAY_AGENT_ID=<AGENT-NAME> \
DATABASE_URL=postgres://lore:<password>@100.127.177.103:5432/lore?sslmode=disable \
OPENAI_API_KEY=<key> \
MCP_DEFAULT_PROJECT_ID=<PROJECT-ID> \
npx tsx ~/runtime/agent-lore/src/relay/relay-dispatcher.ts
```

| Variable | Required | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `RELAY_AGENT_ID` | yes | Your `<AGENT-NAME>`; must be unique |
| `DATABASE_URL` | yes | Tailscale-only Postgres connection — include `?sslmode=disable` |
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | yes | Same key the gateway uses |
| `MCP_DEFAULT_PROJECT_ID` | recommended | Falls back to `undefined` |
| `SWITCHBOARD_DATA_DIR` | WSL only | See platform setup notes |

The dispatcher consumes only `capture_request` messages from the inbox — coordination messages are not dispatched.

