## Project Workflow Pattern

Standard DDR → spec → forge delivery loop used across all homelab projects.

### Roles

| Role | Who | Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| Composer | Danny | Vision, high-level architecture, final approval |
| Producer | The agent | Implementation decisions, production code, no hedging |
| Frank | `/senior-qc` | Adversarial QC gate before each phase advance |

### DDR Loop

1. **DDR** — write `docs/specs/<project-id>-ddrs/DDR-NN-slug.md`; update `00-DDR-INDEX.md`
2. **GitHub issue** — one issue per DDR; link in DDR header
3. **`/spec-start`** — produces 5 docs under `docs/specs/<sprint-slug>/`: `01-REQUIREMENTS`, `02-ARCHITECTURE`, `04-ROADMAP`, `05-REVIEW`, `PROGRESS.md`
4. **Frank gate** — `/senior-qc` reviews the spec; block on any hard stop
5. **`/forge-start`** — implements slice by slice; marks tasks complete in `PROGRESS.md`
6. **Frank gate** — `/senior-qc` reviews the implementation; block on any hard stop
7. **PR** — merge; update DDR status to `ACCEPTED (shipped, PR #N)`

### Directory Structure

```
docs/
  specs/
    <project-id>-ddrs/
      00-DDR-INDEX.md        ← living backlog + build-order rationale
      DDR-NN-slug.md
    <sprint-slug>/
      01-REQUIREMENTS.md
      02-ARCHITECTURE.md
      04-ROADMAP.md
      05-REVIEW.md
      PROGRESS.md
```

### Decision Discipline

- Produce, don't hedge. Pick the risk-mitigating path and proceed.
- One Frank gate per major phase — spec complete, then implementation complete.
- Capture every decision, deviation, and HALT to LORE immediately when it happens.
- `PROGRESS.md` is the ground truth for sprint state — update it slice by slice, not at the end.
